from geb gordon bank subject re tuberculosi in article jonathan h lin write i wa wonder what step be be take to prevent the spread of multi-drug resistant tuberculosi i hear that some place be think of incarcerate those with the disease do thi violate the civil right of these individual are there any legal precedent for such action who know in thi legal climate but there be tremendou legal precendent for forcibly quarantine tb patient in sanitarium yr ago it wa do all the time it ha be do sporadically all along in patient who wo take their medicine if you have tb you may find yourself under surveilence of the public health department and you may find they have the legal power to insist you make ymy clinic visit gordon bank skepticism be the chastity of the intellect and geb it be shameful to surrender it too soon 